Episode 226: The Unbelievable Case of the Harvard Body Snatchers

In July 2022 a woman found buckets full of human remains in her basement. The investigation into where these remains came from would quickly lead police to one of the most prestigious universities in the United States.

Episode 225: The Terrible Murder of Dawn Rossignol

When 21-year-old Dawn Rossignol disappeared early one morning on her way to a doctor’s appointment authorities quickly learned that her killer should have been stopped decades before.

Thank you to Delly Mozingo for researching and writing this story!

Read More

Sadie Eck Sadie Eck

Episode 224: The Suspicious Death of Tori Bethel

21-year-old Tori Bethel was found dead in her apartment in 2022 and police failed to investigate her death as a homicide despite overwhelming evidence that it was. This week we had the honor of speaking with her family about the case to get the full picture of just how badly the system failed them and left potential suspects free to hurt more people.
